    &lt;Title&gt;Mammogram appointment&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;GemB&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was diagnosed with breast cancer in 2015. I had my annual check up at the breast clinic in October. I was I would receive an appointment for my annual mammogram for the end of November.  
I hadn't heard anything, so I phoned the Radiology Department.  
I was told an appointment hadn't been made yet and I would receive it in the post.  
The following Monday, I received a phone call from radiology. The person said &quot;I'm phoning about your appointment on Wednesday&quot; (of the same week) and I said I didn't know anything about an appointment , and that I had already phoned on Friday. I explained it was too short notice to attend on the Wednesday.  
I decided to make a complaint, so I phoned and spoke to a senior staff member who told me an appointment letter had been printed that morning. (Monday).  
I said that the there was no way I would have received the letter in time. They later phoned me and offered me an appointment for December, which I accepted.  
This has caused me great anxiety and inconvenience, especially considering a mammogram is a worrying thing to have done in my circumstances.  
I will be writing to my consultant with my concerns about the way I been treated.  
I received no apology from the Radiology Department or the Manager of Radiology.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
